    <HR SIZE=1>
    <DIV CLASS="NORMAL">
    <B>Older News:</B><BR>
    <UL>
      <LI><B>10 Nov 2000</B>:  Dungeon generator released!  <B>Please note:</B>  
          <UL>
            <LI>This generator only implements the random dungeon tables on 
                pages 112-126 of the DMG.
            <LI>The random map builder will often put multiple doors in a 
                room, and sometimes into the same passage. 
            <LI>I cannot put descriptions of monsters from the MM into this
                program, as the contents of the Monster Manual are copyrighted.
                <I>Please do not ask me to do so!</I>
            <LI>Printing will probably be a problem for most people.  If you
                are using Netscape, use the following procedure to print the
                map and description:
                <UL>
                  <LI>Generate a dungeon.  Note the random seed value that is displayed
                      immediately below the map.
                  <LI>Close that window and enter the seed value in the form in the
                      box labelled "Random seed."  Generate the dungeon again.
                  <LI>You should be able to print the dungeon now.
                </UL>
                Note that large maps will be truncated, or "chopped".  To print
                a large map, you will need to right click on the map, say "save image
                as" and save the image as a <B>.png</B> file to your hard drive.  Then,
                open the image in a graphics editor (like Photoshop, GIMP, IrfanView, etc)
                and print it from there.
            <LI>This program uses the treasure generator to compute treasures, and there
                are still bugs in the treasure generator.  I am already aware that some
                item prices are either negative numbers or are inordinately large.
          </UL>
          Sorry about all the caveats, but I ran out of time and couldn't smooth out
          the wrinkles.  I will release the source code soon for those that are
          interested.
    </UL>
    <P>
    If you discover any bugs or discrepancies while using this utility,
    please send them to <A HREF="mailto:jgb3@email.byu.edu">jgb3@email.byu.edu</A>.
    Be sure to include the following items in your message so that I can
    duplicate the error:
    <UL>
      <LI>The current "<B>random seed</B>" value
    </UL>
    If you do not specify even one of the above items in your e-mail, I may not
    be able to duplicate the error you have found.
    </DIV>

